CRYPTOCURRENCY & BLOCKCHAIN NOTES
 
1Ô∏è. Cryptocurrency Exchange
Definition
A cryptocurrency exchange is a digital platform where users can buy, sell, or trade cryptocurrencies using fiat currency or other cryptocurrencies.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Used for trading crypto assets
‚Ä¢	Acts as an intermediary between buyers and sellers
‚Ä¢	Can be centralized or decentralized
‚Ä¢	Supports crypto pairs like BTC/INR, BTC/USDT
________________________________________
2Ô∏è.Types of Cryptocurrency Exchanges
üîπ Centralized Exchange (CEX)
Definition:
A centralized exchange is managed by a central authority/company.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Works under Web2
‚Ä¢	Requires KYC verification
‚Ä¢	User funds are stored in a centralized database
‚Ä¢	Faster transactions
‚Ä¢	Examples: WazirX, CoinDCX
‚Ä¢	In India:
o	30% tax on crypto profit
o	1% TDS applicable
________________________________________
üîπ Decentralized Exchange (DEX)
Definition:
A decentralized exchange allows peer-to-peer trading without a central authority.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Works under Web3
‚Ä¢	No KYC required
‚Ä¢	Users control their own wallets
‚Ä¢	Uses smart contracts
‚Ä¢	More secure and transparent
‚Ä¢	Examples: Uniswap, PancakeSwap
‚Ä¢	Coin-to-coin swap (e.g., BTC ‚Üí Avalanche)
________________________________________
üîπ International Exchange
Definition:
An international exchange allows trading using global stablecoins.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Trading pairs like BTC/USDT
‚Ä¢	Mostly uses USD-based stablecoins
‚Ä¢	Operates globally
________________________________________
3Ô∏è.Blockchain Transaction Process
Person A (Sender)
        |
        | 1. Transaction Created
        |    (Amount + Receiver Address
        |     + Digital Signature)
        ‚Üì
Transaction Broadcast
to Peer-to-Peer Network
        ‚Üì
Nodes Verify Transaction
(Signature, Balance,
 Double Spending)
        ‚Üì
Valid Transactions
(Mempool / Pending Pool)
        ‚Üì
Miners Select Transactions
        ‚Üì
Block Creation
(Transaction + Previous
 Block Hash + Merkle Root)
        ‚Üì
Proof of Work
(Cryptographic Puzzle
 + Nonce Finding)
        ‚Üì
New Block Found
        ‚Üì
Block Broadcast to All Nodes
        ‚Üì
Nodes Verify Block
        ‚Üì
Block Added to Blockchain
        ‚Üì
Transaction Confirmed
        ‚Üì
Person B (Receiver)
Definition
A blockchain transaction is a process where crypto is transferred from one wallet to another and verified by the network.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Transaction is requested
‚Ä¢	Goes to pending pool
‚Ä¢	Verified by nodes
‚Ä¢	Added into a block
‚Ä¢	Block is broadcast to all nodes
‚Ä¢	Stored permanently on blockchain
________________________________________
4Ô∏è.Block in Blockchain
Definition
A block is a container that stores a group of verified transactions.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Bitcoin block size: 1 MB
‚Ä¢	Each block is linked to the previous block
‚Ä¢	Contains:
o	Transaction data
o	Previous block hash
o	Nonce
‚Ä¢	Shared with every node in the network
________________________________________
5Ô∏è. Nodes and Miners
Node
A node is a computer that maintains and verifies blockchain data.
Miner
A miner verifies transactions and creates new blocks.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Nodes ensure decentralization
‚Ä¢	Miners solve cryptographic puzzles
‚Ä¢	Miners receive rewards in cryptocurrency
________________________________________
6Ô∏è. Nonce
Definition
A nonce is a random number used in mining to solve cryptographic puzzles.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Changes for every mining attempt
‚Ä¢	Helps generate a valid block hash
‚Ä¢	If input changes ‚Üí hash changes
________________________________________
7Ô∏è. Consensus Mechanism
Definition
A consensus mechanism is a method used to agree on the validity of transactions in a blockchain network.
Types & Key Points
üîπ Proof of Work (PoW)
‚Ä¢	Used in Bitcoin
‚Ä¢	Requires heavy computation
‚Ä¢	24/7 mining
‚Ä¢	High energy consumption
üîπ Proof of Stake (PoS)
‚Ä¢	Based on token staking
‚Ä¢	Less energy consumption
‚Ä¢	Faster than PoW
üîπ Proof of Authority (PoA)
‚Ä¢	Based on trusted validators
üîπ Proof of Learning (PoL)
‚Ä¢	Based on learning models
üîπ Delegated Proof of Stake (DPoS)
‚Ä¢	Validators elected by token holders
________________________________________
8Ô∏è.Bitcoin Halving
Definition
Bitcoin halving is an event where the mining reward is reduced by half every 4 years.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Controls Bitcoin supply
‚Ä¢	Often leads to bull runs
‚Ä¢	Halving history:
o	2008 ‚Üí 50 BTC
o	2012 ‚Üí 25 BTC
o	2016 ‚Üí 12.5 BTC
o	2020 ‚Üí 6.25 BTC
o	2024 ‚Üí 3.125 BTC
________________________________________
9Ô∏è. NFT (Non-Fungible Token)
Definition
An NFT is a unique digital asset that cannot be replaced or duplicated.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Non-fungible = not interchangeable
‚Ä¢	Represents ownership
‚Ä¢	Examples:
o	Digital art
o	Photos
o	Videos
o	Digital signatures
‚Ä¢	Built on blockchain
‚Ä¢	Each NFT is unique
________________________________________
10.Fungible Token
Definition
A fungible token is a digital asset where each unit has the same value.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Interchangeable
‚Ä¢	Examples:
o	INR
o	Dollar
o	Bitcoin
‚Ä¢	Built using standards like ERC-20
________________________________________
11.DeFi (Decentralized Finance)
Definition
DeFi refers to financial services built on blockchain without intermediaries like banks.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Built mainly on Ethereum
‚Ä¢	Uses smart contracts
‚Ä¢	Services include:
o	Lending
o	Borrowing
o	Trading
‚Ä¢	Peer-to-peer transactions
‚Ä¢	No central authority
