12.Decentralized Applications (DApps)
Definition
A DApp (Decentralized Application) is an application that runs on a blockchain network instead of a central server.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Built using Ethereum blockchain
‚Ä¢	Uses smart contracts
‚Ä¢	Requires coding and programming languages
‚Ä¢	Examples:
o	Finance apps
o	Chat applications
o	Wallets
‚Ä¢	Data is stored on blockchain
More secure and transparent
________________________________________
13. Smart Contract
Definition
A smart contract is a self-executing program stored on the blockchain.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Written using coding languages
‚Ä¢	Automatically executes rules
‚Ä¢	Transparent and secure
‚Ä¢	Mostly used on Ethereum blockchain
________________________________________
14.Metaverse
Definition
The Metaverse is a virtual digital world where users can interact, work, and trade using digital assets and blockchain technology.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Uses blockchain for ownership and security
‚Ä¢	Connected with NFTs and digital assets
‚Ä¢	Enables virtual interaction and commerce
