15.SHA (Secure Hash Algorithm)
Definition
SHA is a cryptographic algorithm used to generate a unique hash value.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Every transaction has a unique hash
‚Ä¢	Hash cannot be altered
‚Ä¢	Small change in input ‚Üí completely different hash
‚Ä¢	Provides security and immutability
________________________________________
16.Genesis Block
Definition
The genesis block is the first block of a blockchain.
Key Points
‚Ä¢	Has no previous block
‚Ä¢	Starting point of blockchain
‚Ä¢	Followed by all other blocks
